    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1929-04-25T23:59:59-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1929-04-25T00:00:00-05:00" n="267"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d267">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">811.3394/90</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The Chargé in Japan</hi> (<persName type="from">
                        <hi rend="italic">Neville</hi>
                    </persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of
                            State</gloss>
                    </hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Tokyo</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1929-04-25">April 25,
                            1929</date>.<lb/>[Received May 11.]</dateline>
                    <seg rendition="#left">No. 1156</seg>
                </opener>
                <p>
                    <hi rend="smallcaps">Sir</hi>: Referring to the Department’s telegram No. 30 of
                    April 10, 1929, 5 p.m., supplementing my telegram No. 40 of April 19, 1929, 4
                        p.m.,<note n="36" xml:id="d267fn36">Neither printed.</note> regarding the
                    proposed visits to certain Japanese mandated islands of the U. S. S: <hi
                        rend="italic">Asheville</hi>, I have the honor to transmit herewith a copy
                    of my note No. 477 of April 12, 1929, sent to the Foreign Office in compliance
                    with the Department’s telegram under reference. No reply has been received from
                    the Foreign Office but on April 19th Mr. Matsunaga, the Chief of the Treaty
                    Bureau, called on me at the Embassy and said that he came on behalf of Mr.
                    Yoshida, the Vice Minister.</p>
                <p>He told me that the Foreign Office had referred our inquiry in regard to the
                    desire of the United States Navy to send the U. S. S. <hi rend="italic"
                        >Asheville</hi> to various ports and islands in the Japanese mandate
                    territory to the South Seas Bureau of the Japanese Government. The <pb
                        facs="0375" n="257" xml:id="pg_257"/> South Seas Bureau had stated that
                    while they would be very glad to have a visit from the United States Man-of-War
                    at any of the open ports, namely, Saipan, Angaur, Truck, and Jaluit, they could
                    not see their way to welcoming visits of this kind to out of the way places
                    because harbor accommodations were limited in these small islands, there were no
                    pilots available, and these harbors or anchorages were difficult of approach and
                    at times dangerous. I said that I would transmit this information, which I
                    thought was rather disappointing, to the Navy.</p>
                <p>After some desultory conversation in which I referred to our disappointment at
                    the South Seas Bureau’s decision—without any apparent effect on Mr. Matsunaga—he
                    took his leave.</p>
                <p>I have [etc.]</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Edwin L. Neville</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
                <frus:attachment>
                    <opener>
                        <seg rendition="#center">[Enclosure]</seg>
                    </opener>
                    <head>
                        <hi rend="italic">The American Chargé</hi> (<persName type="from">
                            <hi rend="italic">Neville</hi>
                        </persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the Japanese Minister for Foreign
                            Affairs</hi> (<persName type="to">
                            <hi rend="italic">Tanaka</hi>
                        </persName>)</head>
                    <opener>
                        <dateline rendition="#right">
                            <placeName>
                                <hi rend="smallcaps">Tokyo</hi>
                            </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1929-04-12">April 12,
                                1929</date>.</dateline>
                        <seg rendition="#left">No. 477</seg>
                    </opener>
                    <p>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Excellency</hi>: Under instructions from my Government
                        I have the honor to inform Your Excellency that the United States Navy
                        Department contemplates ordering the U. S. S. <hi rend="italic"
                            >Asheville</hi> to leave Manila about April 25th for return to the
                        United States via Guam and Honolulu and to visit for about three days in
                        each case the following islands of the Japanese Mandate en route: <table
                            cols="2" rend="width: 85%:" rendition="#center-block" rows="7">
                            <row>
                                <cell>Angaur Island</cell>
                                <cell>April 30th</cell>
                            </row>
                            <row>
                                <cell>Oleai (or Ulie) Island</cell>
                                <cell>May 6th</cell>
                            </row>
                            <row>
                                <cell>Ujeland Atoll</cell>
                                <cell>May 21st</cell>
                            </row>
                            <row>
                                <cell>Kwajalong Atoll</cell>
                                <cell>May 26th</cell>
                            </row>
                            <row>
                                <cell>Udia Atoll</cell>
                                <cell>May 29th</cell>
                            </row>
                            <row>
                                <cell>Maloalab Kaoven</cell>
                                <cell>June 2nd</cell>
                            </row>
                            <row>
                                <cell>Wotje Atoll</cell>
                                <cell>June 5th</cell>
                            </row>
                        </table>
                    </p>
                    <p>In bringing the foregoing to the notice of Your Excellency I was further
                        instructed to inquire whether the proposed visits would be agreeable to the
                        authorities concerned.</p>
                    <p>I avail myself [etc.]</p>
                    <closer>
                        <signed>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Edwin L. Neville</hi>
                        </signed>
                    </closer>
                </frus:attachment>
            </div>
